  "key_findings": [
    "Signal extraction works: models prefer correct answers despite seeing contradictions (J1: 65%→75%→81%→85%)",
    "Strong scaling: accuracy increases monotonically with model size for all random conditions",
    "Coherent errors: J2 stable around 45-51% across all sizes — compression cannot distinguish coherent errors from truth",
    "J2 large = 51%: at large scale coherent errors are at chance, not below — size eliminates the slight coherent preference",
    "Graceful degradation with noise ratio: J1 > J3 > J4 > J5 at every model size",
    "J5 (no correct data): 54-60% — models detect structural regularities even without correct examples, but effect weakens with size",
    "Denoising accuracy approaches standard: large denoising 85.2% vs standard 89.1% — contradictions reduce but don't eliminate truth bias",
    "J4 plateau: accuracy ~66% for medium and large, suggesting 1:4 noise ratio is near the limit for this architecture"
  ]
